# Winter Festival Countdown App - Goose Hints

## Project Overview
A festive countdown timer web application for the Winter Festival with rotating facts and email signup.

## Technology Stack
- **Frontend**: Vanilla HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (ES6+)
- **No frameworks**: Keep it simple and performant
- **Storage**: localStorage for email signups (Stage 1-8)
- **Deployment**: Static hosting (Netlify, Vercel, GitHub Pages)

## Code Style & Conventions

### JavaScript
- Use ES6+ features (const/let, arrow functions, template literals)
- Prefer functional programming patterns
- Use meaningful variable names (e.g., `countdownTimer`, not `ct`)
- Add comments for complex logic
- Keep functions small and focused (single responsibility)
- No console.logs in production code

### CSS
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Use CSS custom properties for colors and spacing
- BEM naming convention for classes (e.g., `countdown__timer--large`)
- Group related styles together
- Comment sections clearly

### HTML
- Semantic HTML5 elements
- Accessible markup (ARIA labels where needed)
- Meta tags for SEO and social sharing
- Clean indentation (2 spaces)

## File Organization
```
day-16/
├── .goosehints          # This file
├── README.md            # Project documentation
├── TODO.md              # Task tracking
├── PRD.md               # Product requirements
├── index.html           # Main HTML file
├── css/
│   ├── styles.css       # Main styles
│   ├── responsive.css   # Media queries
│   └── animations.css   # Animations and transitions
├── js/
│   ├── countdown.js     # Countdown timer logic
│   ├── facts.js         # Fun facts rotation
│   └── form.js          # Email form handling
├── assets/
│   ├── images/          # Images and icons
│   └── fonts/           # Custom fonts (if needed)
└── docs/
    └── deployment.md    # Deployment guide
```

## Design Guidelines

### Color Palette (Winter Theme)
- Primary: Ice blue (#5AB9EA, #4A90E2)
- Secondary: Snow white (#FFFFFF, #F8F9FA)
- Accent: Silver (#C0C0C0, #E8E8E8)
- Text: Dark slate (#2C3E50, #34495E)
- Gradient backgrounds encouraged

### Typography
- Headings: Clean, modern sans-serif (system fonts preferred)
- Body: Readable, accessible fonts
- Minimum font size: 16px for body text
- Line height: 1.6 for readability

### Spacing
- Use consistent spacing scale (8px base)
- Mobile padding: 16px
- Desktop padding: 24px-32px

## Development Workflow
1. Build features incrementally (one stage at a time)
2. Test in browser after each change
3. Ensure mobile responsiveness throughout
4. Keep TODO.md updated with progress
5. Commit working code frequently

## Testing Checklist
- [ ] Works in Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge
- [ ] Responsive on mobile (320px+), tablet, desktop
- [ ] Countdown updates accurately
- [ ] Facts rotate smoothly
- [ ] Form validation works
- [ ] Email storage persists
- [ ] Accessible (keyboard navigation, screen readers)
- [ ] Fast load time (<2s)

## Accessibility Standards
- Use semantic HTML
- Include ARIA labels for interactive elements
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Maintain 4.5:1 color contrast ratio
- Add alt text for images
- Test with screen reader

## Performance Goals
- Initial load: <2 seconds
- Smooth 60fps animations
- Minimal JavaScript bundle
- Optimize images (WebP format preferred)
- Lazy load non-critical assets

## Deployment
- Static site deployment (Netlify/Vercel preferred)
- Environment variables for any API keys
- HTTPS required
- Custom domain optional

## Notes for Goose
- Prefer simplicity over complexity
- Write clean, readable code
- Explain complex logic with comments
- Test incrementally as you build
- Ask for clarification if requirements are unclear
- Focus on one stage at a time per the PRD
